hint.description: Every system connected to a network uses ports. Those ports are numbered. Look into Secure Shell Protocol

Assuming you're using linux, look into proper usage of the ssh command, something along the lines of
ssh \<username\>@\<ip\>
There's a surprising amount of unsecured systems using Default credentials. These Default credentials make systems easily accessible. Try searching some DEFAULT credentials and see what happens
